62.1	Leslie_speaker	Leslie speaker	The Leslie speaker is a specially constructed amplifier/loudspeaker used to create special audio effects using the Doppler effect. Named after its inventor, Donald Leslie, it is particularly associated with the Hammond organ but is used with a variety of instruments as well as vocals. The Hammond/Leslie combination has become an element in many genres of music. The Leslie Speaker and the Hammond Organ brands are currently owned by Suzuki Musical Instrument Corporation.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Leslie_Speaker.jpg/250px-Leslie_Speaker.jpg
